      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>S<sub>N</sub>2 reactions take place with inversion of configuration, and S<sub>N</sub>1 reactions take place with racemization. The following substitution reaction, however, occurs with complete <i>retention</i> of configuration. Propose a mechanism. (Hint: two inversions = retention.)</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBdGNUIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--e47856c24e0bdbb5ab05c5d59eb66bf8e833f87f/OChem_11_EC_022.jpg\" alt=\"The reaction of (R)-2-bromopropanoic acid first with one percent sodium hydroxide and water, and then with hydronium ion, forms (R)-2-hydroxypropanoic acid.\">",
